definition:
A man of the tribe of Levi  living at the time of Exile and Return, first mentioned at 1Ch.9.12; 
 son of: Jahzerah (H3170); 
 father of: Maasai (H4640); also called Azarel (KJV: Azareel) at Neh.11.13;
Also named: a.zar.el (עֲזַרְאֵל "Azarel" H5832K)
 § Adiel = "ornament of God"
1) a prince of the Simeon of the family of Shimei in the time of king Hezekiah of Judah
2) a priest, ancestor of Maasiai
3) ancestor of Azmaveth, the treasurer of David
